1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. Bd3 $5 {The position has become close to the modern Caro-Kann.} dxe4 4. Bxe4 Nf6 5. Nc3 Nxe4 6. Nxe4 Bf5 7. Ng3 Bg6 8. Nf3 Nd7 9. Nh4 e6 10. Nxg6 hxg6 {The position has become close to the modern Caro-Kann.} 11. Bf4 Nf6 12. Qd2 Nd5 13. Ne4 $6 ({Better is} 13. O-O-O Nxf4 14. Qxf4) 13... Qh4 $1 {Duras assaults the vulnerable pieces.} 14. Nd6+ Bxd6 15. Bxd6 Rd8 $5 16. Bg3 $6 (16. Be5 $1 Qe4+ 17. Kf1 $1 {brings counter- play.}) 16... Qe4+ 17. Kf1 Nb6 18. c3 c5 19. Rd1 cxd4 20. cxd4 Rc8 21. Qe2 Qf5 22. Be5 O-O 23. g4 $5 Qc2 24. Rd2 $2 {White gives a pawn.} (24. h4 {aims at a difficult endgame.}) 24... Qb1+ 25. Kg2 Qxa2 26. h4 Qd5+ 27. f3 Nc4 28. Rd3 Qb5 29. Rd2 Qa4 30. b3 $5 Qxb3 31. Rd3 Qb5 32. h5 Nxe5 33. dxe5 gxh5 34. Qe3 $5 (34. Rxh5 Rc3 $1 {leads to exchanges.}) 34... Rc2+ 35. Kg3 Qb2 36. Rxh5 Rg2+ 37. Kf4 f6 38. Qc5 fxe5+ {Duras was catching up on Mieses.} 0-1


