1. e4 {1) Lasker:The international congress St.Petersburg 1909.Translation by R.Teichmann (2) Lasker: Der internationale Schachkongreß zu St.Petersburg. 1909. Berlin.1909. (Nachdruck Olms.1989.)} e5 2. Nc3 Bc5 3. g3 Nf6 4. Bg2 c6 {The slow line of play selected by Duras, is answered quite correctly on the part of Mieses by the isolation of the d-pawn.} ({Here Black might very well play} 4... d5) 5. Nge2 d5 6. exd5 Nxd5 7. Nxd5 cxd5 8. d4 exd4 9. Nxd4 O-O 10. O-O Bb6 11. Be3 Nc6 12. Qd2 Ne5 13. b3 Bh3 14. Rad1 Bxg2 15. Kxg2 Rc8 16. Rfe1 $2 {A regrettably gross blunder, which throws away the fruit of his consistent and logical play.} (16. Ne2 $142 {would have been very strong. He should change the Black KB, in order to secure the position of the Knight at d4. e.g.} Bxe3 (16... Ng4 {would probably be a little better.}) 17. Qxe3 Nc6 18. c4 Re8 19. Qf3 d4 20. Nf4) (16. Nb5 $142 $14) 16... Ba5 17. b4 Nc4 18. Qc1 Bxb4 19. c3 Ba3 20. Qc2 Qd7 21. Qb3 Bc5 22. Nc2 Qf5 23. Bxc5 Rxc5 24. Re7 Na5 25. Qa3 b6 26. Ne3 Qc8 27. Rxa7 Rxc3 28. Qd6 Rxe3 29. Qxb6 Nc4 30. Qb5 Re2 31. Kf1 Rfe8 32. Kg1 Qh3 0-1


