{Played 2nd August 1904.} 1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. Nc3 e6 4. Nf3 Bb4 5. exd5 exd5 6. Bd3 Bg4 (6... Nf6 7. Qe2+ Be7 8. O-O $11) 7. O-O $14 Ne7 8. Bf4 f6 9. Na4 O-O 10. h3 Bc8 (10... Bh5 $142 $5 $11) 11. c3 $16 Bd6 12. Bg3 Nf5 13. Qc2 g6 (13... Nxg3 14. fxg3 f5 $11) 14. Nh2 $6 (14. Bxd6 $142 Qxd6 15. Rfe1 $14) 14... Bxg3 $17 15. fxg3 $17 Ne3 16. Qd2 Nxf1 17. Rxf1 Rf7 18. h4 Qd6 19. Qh6 Nd7 20. h5 g5 (20... gxh5 $142 21. Qxh5 Nf8 $19 (21... Qxg3 22. Ng4 Kf8 23. Rf3 Qe1+ 24. Kh2 $14)) 21. Rf5 $6 Qf8 (21... b5 $5 22. Ng4 (22. Nc5 Nxc5 $19) 22... bxa4 $19) 22. Ng4 Kh8 23. Rf2 Qxh6 (23... b5 $142 24. Qxf8+ Rxf8 $19) 24. Nxh6 $17 Rf8 (24... Re7 $142 25. b3 Nb6 $19) 25. Re2 f5 26. Re7 b5 (26... Nf6 $5 $15) 27. Bxf5 Nf6 28. Nf7+ Kg7 29. Ne5+ Kg8 30. Bxc8 Raxc8 31. Nc5 {At last! The game is soon turned in White's favour now that his queen's knight is back in play.} Rfe8 32. Rxa7 Nxh5 33. Ng4 Ra8 34. Rc7 Rf8 (34... Re2 35. Kh2 $11) 35. a3 $11 (35. Ne6 $5 Rac8 36. Rd7 $16) 35... Kh8 $2 (35... Rae8 $142 $5 36. Nh6+ Kh8 37. Nf7+ Kg8 38. Nxg5 Rf6 $11) 36. Rxc6 $16 Ra7 $2 (36... Nxg3 $14) (36... Rae8 37. Kh2 Rf1 $16) 37. Kh2 $18 {White is now winning after two consecutive bad moves by Black.} Ng7 38. Rd6 h5 39. Rh6+ Kg8 40. Nf6+ Kf7 41. Nxd5 Rd8 42. Nb4 Re8 43. Nc6 Rc7 44. d5 Kg8 (44... Nf5 {Sets a trap.} 45. Rh7+ (45. Rxh5 $2 Kg6 46. Rh3 Ne3 $11) 45... Ng7 46. b4 $16) 45. g4 hxg4 46. Rg6 Kh7 47. Rxg5 Re2 48. Rxg4 Rd2 {(D)} 49. Ne4 Re2 (49... Rxd5 {was the only chance to obtain some counterplay} 50. Nf6+ Kh6 51. Nxd5 Rxc6 $18) 50. Ne5 Ne8 51. d6 Rg7 52. Rxg7+ Nxg7 53. d7 Ne6 (53... Rxe4 54. d8=Q Rxe5 $18) 54. Ng5+ $1 {A deflection sacrifice to queen the pawn.} Nxg5 55. d8=Q {(Source: TB, p.127)} (55. d8=Q Rxe5 56. Qc7+ Kg6 57. Qxe5 $18) 1-0


