1. e4 {1) Lasker:The international congress St.Petersburg 1909. Translation by R.Teichmann (2) Lasker: Der internationale Schachkongreß zu St.Petersburg. 1909. Berlin.1909. (Nachdruck Olms.1989.)} e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 Nf6 5. O-O Be7 6. d3 b5 7. Bb3 d6 8. c3 Bg4 9. a4 Na5 {The advantage of this flanking movement of the Knight is not clear.} ({Why not} 9... O-O {and prepare either f5 or d5?}) 10. Bc2 h6 11. d4 Nd7 12. Qe2 O-O $2 {A gross blunder.} ({He had nothing better than} 12... c6) 13. axb5 axb5 14. Qxb5 Bxf3 15. Rxa5 Rxa5 16. Qxa5 Bg5 17. Be3 ({It is clear that after} 17. gxf3 Bxc1 18. Rxc1 $2 {Black would win with} Qg5+) ({but with} 17. Nd2 {he would have avoided the hampering doubled Pawn, which results from this move.}) 17... Bh5 18. Qb5 Bxe3 19. fxe3 Qg5 $2 {He throws his only chance away by despair.} ({Why did he not play} 19... f6 {preventing White at least for a long time, from turning his extra Pawn to account?}) (19... Bg6 $142 20. Nd2 Nf6 21. Qc6 Qb8 22. b3 Qa8 23. Qxa8 Rxa8 24. Bb1 Ra3 25. Kf2 d5 $132) 20. Qxd7 $18 Qxe3+ 21. Kh1 Qe2 22. Qf5 Qxc2 23. Qxh5 exd4 24. Qd1 Qxe4 25. Qxd4 Qxd4 26. cxd4 Rb8 27. Rf2 Re8 28. Nd2 Re1+ 29. Nf1 Rd1 30. Kg1 Rxd4 31. Rc2 c5 32. Rd2 Rb4 33. Ne3 g6 34. Nd5 Rb3 35. Nf6+ 1-0


