1. d4 {1) Lasker:The international congress St.Petersburg 1909. Translation by R.Teichmann (2) Lasker: Der internationale Schachkongreß zu St.Petersburg. 1909. Berlin.1909. (Nachdruck Olms.1989.)} d5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. c4 dxc4 4. e3 c5 5. Bxc4 e6 6. Nc3 a6 7. O-O b5 8. Bd3 Bb7 9. Qe2 Nbd7 10. Rd1 Qb6 11. Bc2 Rc8 12. a3 {Both players follow approved lines of development.} Be7 13. e4 cxd4 14. Nxd4 Ne5 15. Bg5 O-O 16. Nf3 Qc5 17. Be3 Qc4 {A forcible move.} 18. Nxe5 ({If} 18. Qxc4 Nxc4 {Black threatens xb2 or xe4 or xa3}) 18... Qxe2 19. Nxe2 Rxc2 20. Nd4 Rc5 (20... Rxb2 $2 {would be a gross blunder because of} 21. Nd3 $18) 21. Nd3 Rc4 22. f3 Rd8 23. Nb3 {Black's c5 and a5 are weak.} Rc2 24. Bc5 Kf8 25. Bxe7+ Kxe7 26. Na5 Rc7 27. Nb4 Rxd1+ 28. Rxd1 Ba8 29. Kf2 Ne8 30. Ke3 Nd6 31. Rd2 f5 32. exf5 Nxf5+ 33. Kf2 Bd5 {Black is in a difficulty, and therefore decides on a desperate sacrifice of a pawn, in order to render the Bishop mobile.} 34. Nxa6 {is strongest} (34. Rxd5 {was also feasible. But after the exchanges} exd5 35. Nxd5+ Kd7 36. Nxc7 Kxc7 {Black's King would then have a very favorable position in the center, both for attack on the Queen's side and defense of the King's side.}) 34... Rc1 (34... Ra7 35. Rxd5 Rxa6 (35... exd5 36. Nc6+ $18) 36. Rxb5 $18) 35. Nb4 Kd6 36. Nb3 Rh1 37. h3 Rb1 38. g4 Ne7 39. Nd4 Kc5 {[%mdl 4096]} 40. Ne2 $16 {A mistake.} ({White ought to have clinched matters.} 40. Nxd5 $18 exd5 41. Ne6+ Kc4 42. Nxg7 {and in answer to} d4 ({or} 42... Kb3 43. Nf5 {the game might then have developed} Nc6 44. Nd6) (42... Rh1 43. Ne6 Rxh3 44. Rc2+ Kd3 45. Rc3+ Kd2 46. Nd4 $18) 43. Nf5 Nc6 44. Nd6+ Kb3 45. Nxb5 Rxb2 46. Ke2 $1 $18 {and whilst the d-pawn would now be paralyzed, White's Pawns would become very dangerous.}) 40... Rh1 41. Kg2 Ra1 42. Rc2+ Bc4 43. Nc3 Nd5 44. Ne4+ Kd4 ({He ought to have gone to b6.} 44... Kb6 $142 {White would, in this case, have had no alternative but to try for a doubtful win by} 45. Nxd5+ exd5 46. Nd2 g5 $11 {White would probably have had to sacrifice his h-pawn.} 47. h4 gxh4 48. f4 Re1 49. Kh3 Rh1+ 50. Kg2 Re1) 45. Rxc4+ Kxc4 46. Nd2+ Kd4 47. Nb3+ Ke3 48. Nxd5+ exd5 49. Nxa1 Kd2 50. Nb3+ Ke3 51. h4 g6 52. Kg3 Kd3 53. Kf4 Kc4 54. Nc1 1-0


